    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>?] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-07">December 7,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for: The Secretary of State.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After discussing this matter<note n="1" xml:id="d505fn1">See <persName
                            corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName>’s letter of November 21, 1943, to
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> (<hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_266">p. 266</ref>), on the question of
                        making Rome an open city. See also <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_801">p. 801</ref>.</note> with the British military
                    authorities I consider it inadvisable to reopen the matter at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi
                                rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
